gmd:identificationInfo.gmd:MD_DataIdentification.gmd:abstract.gco:CharacterString.#text:§Data of type chemistry measured on Dardennes - Le Las basin within the framework of the PORT-MIOU observatory, that is part of the KARST observatory network. The KARST observatory network aims to strengthen knowledge-sharing and to promote cross-disciplinary research on karst systems, in the framework of the OZCAR Critical Zone network Research Infrastructure.
Data consist in 2 time series on 1 station(s). 
The measured parameters are: Conductivity (mS/cm), Water temperature (°C).
Measurements start on 19-10-2012 and end on 16-03-2019
